summary: You sighed when you looked at the time. An hour had officially passed since your date was supposed to meet you for dinner. You...
body:
“Stand Up Date” A Brie Larson imagine

You sighed when you looked at the time. An hour had officially passed since your date was supposed to meet you for dinner. You felt like an idiot for waiting, but you really liked the person and hoped they were running late. Just as you were about to call the waiter over to get the bill for your drink, a woman approached your table.

“Hi, this is going to sound super weird and if you want to say no it’s one hundred percent okay. May I sit with you? My friend just bailed on me and I don’t want to have dinner alone.”

“Uh…sure.” You couldn’t believe what you just said. You were really going to let a stranger have dinner with you.

“Thank you! You’re amazing.” The woman sat down in the seat intended for your date. You couldn’t help but notice how pretty she was and how familiar she seemed to you.

“Have you ordered yet?” She asked while intensely scanning the menu.

“No, I was um-I was waiting for my date. But they didn’t show up.” The woman’s head snapped up and she actually looked angry.

“You were stood up?”

“Yeah. It’s like they say, there’s a first time for everything.” You shrugged, not wanting her to pity you.

“Well, it’s their loss. You look amazing.”

“Oh…thank you. You look amazing as well.”

“Thanks. So, what are you going to get?”

“I’m not sure. I’ve never been here before.”

“Seriously?! You should try the salad and fries. I know it’s a weird combination, but it’s good.”

You sat in silence while trying to decide what to order for a few minutes. The waiter came over, probably assuming that your date had finally arrived, and took your orders. You went with the stranger’s advice and got the salad and fries.

“If we’re going to have dinner together, we should probably introduce ourselves. I’m Brie and I’m an actress.” The woman extended her hand across the table and you quickly shook it.

“I’m y/n and I work in a boring office. Nice to meet you, Brie.”

“It’s nice to meet you too, y/n. So, how was your day?”

“It was okay, work was boring as usual. How about you? How was your day?”

“It was alright. I’m working on a new script right now so I spent a majority of my day at home.”

“You act and a write? That’s really cool.”

“I attempt to write. I can write like two sentences then I re-read them, hate them, and eventually start over. I’m a much better actress.” In that moment, you realized why she seemed so familiar. She was Brie Larson the academy award winning actress. You wanted to freak out, but you managed to keep your shock under wraps.

“Acting must be fun. You probably get to travel a lot and meet cool people.”

“It’s fun for the most part. Sometimes I think it’s hard to be away from my family.”

“I understand that. Most of my family lives out East so I’m kind of on my own out here.” You said, mentally kicking yourself because Brie was defiantly going to feel bad for you. Brie looked at you for a moment before reaching across the table and supportively holding your hand.

“I know we just met, but I feel like we’re going to be friends. If you ever want to talk, I’ll be here to listen.”

“Thank you, really, Brie.”

“It’s no problem, y/n.”

The two of you continued to talk even when your food arrived. You mostly talked rather than eat. Neither one of you wanted to miss anything the other said. When it came time to pay the bill, Brie nonchalantly handed her credit card to the waiter that way you two could continue talking about Malibu.

However, when it was time to say goodbye, you really took your time. You stayed at the table for ten minutes after Brie payed and then slowly walked to your car. Once you reached your car, you leaned against it while facing Brie.

“Thank you for turning my terrible night around.”

“The pleasure was all mine. I had fun tonight.”

“I did too. We should hang out again.”

“We defiantly should. Can I give you my number?”

“Yes of course.”

You quickly pulled your phone out and created a new contact for Brie. She looked so concentrated while typing her number in it almost look like she was taking a test.

“Will you text me when you make it home? I like to make sure my friends get home safe.”

“Of course I will.”

“Great. I’ll see you later?”

“Yeah you will.”

Brie gave you one last smile before walking to her own car. You got into your car and tried to make sense of what had happened. You were stood up and Brie Larson showed up to make you feel like less of a loser. It was a crazy situation, something that only happened in story books or cheesy made for tv movies.

With a smile on your face, you pulled out of the parking lot and drove home. Once you were safely in your home with all the doors and windows locked, you texted Brie (and noticed the emojis by her name)

Y/n: Hi! Just letting you know I made it home safe and sound

Brie 🤙🏻💖: Hey! I’m glad you’re home safe, I just walked through my front door

Y/n: Well I’m glad you’re home safe too. Goodnight Brie

Brie 🤙🏻💖: Goodnight y/n
